The paper deals with the time and crossing sequence complexities of one-tape off-line Turing machines, which are topics related to formal languages (cs.FL) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of crossing sequences also suggests a connection to discrete structures (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the mention of efficient implementations of algorithms suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
